rComments: An amazing person, but his lecture style could use some work. He's really great at sharing personal experiences, but the rest of the content is very dry. A lot of people chose to skip class because they could just memorize the textbook or the slides. The MC exams are also on the excessively tedious side, but his short answers are extremely fair.

This professor is amazing! He replies to emails really quickly, is always willing to help & is pretty passionate about what he teaches. The course itself is a little bland - but overall the coursework is easy as he provides clearly outlined rubrics & expectations. Lots of writing is involved but mostly opinion pieces & a final lit. review paper

So much work in this class. I know this is a D level but acts like it's the only course you're taking. Two group projects, two fifteen page papers, one of which is with the group but still. Four "reflection" papers. One of the papers he made us read was of course a paper he co authored that was like 30 pages long.
